Florence, Laurie  | Engineering Alumni | University of Illinois at Chicago                     It all starts with a single spark         Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Engineering Alumni      Engineering Alumni   Main Menu    News    Expand News menu           Dean's List    RISE Magazine         Events    Expand Events menu           Upcoming Events         Get Involved    Expand Get Involved menu           Join us on LinkedIn    Become a Mentor    Volunteer    Engineer your own involvement    Honor a Professor         Awards    Expand Awards menu           2019 Alumni Award Honorees    2018 Alumni Award Honorees    2017 Alumni Award Honorees         Give    Contact     Eyebrow menu    College of Engineering    Engineering Career Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                           Laurie  Florence  Champion's Award  Major: Electrical Engineering                About   Laurie Florence has worked for Underwriters Laboratories, Inc. (now UL LLC) for more than 28 years, starting as an engineer in the electrical department and serving as UL:s principal engineer for batteries, fuel cells systems, and capacitors for the last 15 years. As principal engineer, Laurie's recent focus has been on large-scale battery systems for both stationary and motive applications and energy storage systems. She is responsible for the technical input in her areas of responsibility, including technical competency of staff and the development and maintenance of the certification categories and standards. Laurie also presents at various technical forums and industry trade shows and participates on a number of safety and performance standards development committees for various organizations as UL:s technical representative. She is also the convener for a subcommittee that deals with lithium-ion battery standards for industrial applications within the International Electrotechnical Commission. Laurie graduated from UIC in 1990 with a BS in electrical engineering and is a board member-at-large for the UIC Engineering Alumni Association. She resides in Chicago with her husband and two dogs and has three children, the youngest of whom is also an alumnus of UIC.                    UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni       Contact   851 S. Morgan - SEO Rm. 811  Phone: 3129969422  MWilli60@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 